 Chavez''s socialist government turned a blind eye, and now about 3,000 people call the tower their home. Picture taken February 9, 2014. REUTERS/Jorge Silva (VENEZUELA - Tags: SOCIETY POVERTY BUSINESS)\r\n\r\nATTENTION EDITORS: PICTURE 17 OF 35 FOR PACKAGE ''VENEZUELA''S SKYSCRAPER SLUM'' \r\nTO FIND ALL IMAGES SEARCH ''TOWER OF DAVID'' - RTR3JLNB";s:17:"created_timestamp";i:0;s:9:"copyright";s:0:"";s:12:"focal_length";i:0;s:3:"iso";i:0;s:13:"shutter_speed";i:0;s:5:"title";s:96:"Rivas lifts weights on a balcony on the 28th floor of the "Tower of David" skyscraper in Caracas";}}'),
